# ZCode → llm-coding-bridge
#
# ZCode speaks the OpenAI Chat Completions API (apiFormat:
# openai-chat-completions) and has no client-side idle/stream timeout knob, so
# the bridge keeps the connection alive with an SSE `: ping` comment frame
# every 15s while the upstream is "thinking" before its first byte. Configure
# the interval with server.heartbeatIntervalMs (0 disables it).
#
# In ZCode, add a custom OpenAI-compatible provider with these values:
#   kind:     openai-compatible
#   baseURL:  http://127.0.0.1:37629/v1
#   apiKey:   <your upstream API key>   (the bridge forwards it as a Bearer token)
#   model:    your-model
#
# ZCode does not read this file directly; it is reference material.
OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:37629/v1
OPENAI_API_KEY=app-your-upstream-key
OPENAI_MODEL=your-model
